CAPE TOWN - Cape Town residents are being urged to reduce daily water usage by a hundred million litres immediately.The Western Cape is experiencing its worst drought in over 100 years and has been declared a disaster area.READ: Western Cape declared a disaster areaDam levels continue to decline and were on Monday sitting at just over 20 percent.Authorities in Cape Town say they are concerned water usage remains above consumption targets.Residents are also being urged to report water leaks.eNCA